\pard\intbl\ql
{{\b
Aims of the course: }}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{Students acquire comprehensive knowledge of capital markets in market 
economy and their organization, covering the bond and stock markets 
and the activities of institutional investors on the world capital 
markets\'2e The course focuses on three areas closely associated with 
capital market\'2e The first topic is the capital market in a market 
economy, its structure, functions, importance and system, methods 
and instruments of regulation and supervision\'2e The second area 
relates to investment instruments trading on the capital markets, 
their characteristic features and principles of valuation\'2e The 
third issue focuses on capital markets investors, including its incentives, 
criterions, activities, position and importance\'2e}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{\~}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{{\b
Learning outcomes and competences: }}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{Upon successful completion of this course, students will be able to: 
\line
\_ understand how capital markets work and what their functions in 
market economy are;\line
\_ describe and compare selected world exchanges, including Prague 
Stock Exchange and RM\_System;\line
\_ calculate return, risk and liquidity of different investment instruments;\line
\_ valuate stock or bond using elementary methods, procedures and 
fundamental analysis models;\line
\_ apply basic methods, tools and principles of technical and psychological 
analysis on the capital markets;\line
\_ evaluate activities, position and importance of institutional investors 
on capital markets\'2e}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{\~}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{{\b
