}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{1\'2e\tab Role of \'46inancial Markets and Institutions in economy\'2e 
Basic principles, functions, structure and importance of capital markets 
(savings allocation, capital market characteristics,capital market 
structure, capital market position on economy)\'2e\line
2\'2e\tab Capital market regulation and supervision (reason for regulation 
and supervision, methods and instrument of regulation and supervision, 
regulation and supervision in Czech Republic)\'2e\line
3\'2e\tab Trends on the worlds capital markets (basic developing trend 
and related conditions, future of the world capital markets)\'2e\line
4\'2e\tab Bond markets\'2e Bond valuation and basic principles of 
bond analysis\'2e\line
5\'2e\tab Stock markets\'2e Stock valuation\'2e Basic principles fundamental, 
technical a psychological stock analyses\'2e Efficient market theory\'2e\line
6\'2e\tab \'46inancial derivatives markets (options, financial futures, 
swaps, warrants)\'2e New instruments on the capital markets\'2e\line
7\'2e\tab Other investment instruments markets (precious metals market,real 
estates market, art collections market)\'2e\line
8\'2e\tab International capital markets and institutional investors 
(characteristics, investors, instruments, return, risk and liquidity)\'2e\line
9\'2e\tab Primary and secondary markets\'2e Exchange and OTC markets\'2e 
Exchange system and its components\'2e\line
10\'2e\tab Prague Stock Exchange\'2e RM\_system\'2e\line
11\'2e\tab World exchange centre (NYSE, LSE, TSE, EURONEXT)\'2e\line
12\'2e\tab Investment banking (definition of investment banking, institutions 
of investment banking, models of incorporation commercial and investment 
banking, investment services)\'2e\line
13\'2e\tab Collective investing (conception, advantages and disadvantages 
of collective investing, institutions of collective investing, measurement 
of funds performance, collective investing in Czech Republic)\'2e\line
14\'2e\tab Pension funds (pension funds position on the capital markets, 
types of pension plans, investment policy of pension funds, pension 
additional insurance in Czech Republic)\'2e\line
}\cell\row\pard
